The Department of State Security Services, DSS has reacted to reports of alleged arrest of Abia senator, Enyinnaya Abaribe for rocking ‘Dot Nation’ T-shirt.  The agency said nothing of that nature ever happened. Recall that on Wednesday, a report went viral on social media that the senator was arrested for wearing a t-shirt with the inscription, ‘dot nation’. Another report alleged that he was arrested at Transcorp Hilton hotel in Abuja during a function. The agency debunked the allegation on Thursday through its spokesperson, Peter Afunanya in a text message, saying “It’s not true pls”.  Source By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Contrary to reports in some online media, (not Sundiata Post), the Federal lawmaker resenting Abia South senatorial district at the National Assembly, Senator Eyinnaya Abaribe has not been released from detention, Sundiata Post authoritatively reports.   Recall that the Department of State Services, DSS,… In "News" Abuja (Precise Post) - An alleged Supporter of the All Progressives Congress, APC has been arrested by the Department of State Security, DSS for vote-buying. The suspect, seen wearing a white Polka dot shirt in the footage below was accused of vote-buying by the electorate at Esan North East LGA,… In "Top Stories" Chairman of Senate Committee on Power, Eyinnanya Abaribe, has raised the alarm over a N30 billion provision allegedly included in the 2018 budget document after the National Assembly (NASS) had approved it. Abaribe, who was arrested and detained by the Department of State Services (DSS) on Friday, told journalists through… In "Business"